label.value: Buttock

value.value: Either of the fleshy mounds in the rear pelvic area of the human body formed by the gluteal muscles.

label.value: Scalp

value.value: The skin which covers the top of the head and which is usually covered by hair.

label.value: Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics

value.value: An international organization with a mission to promote the wellbeing of women and to raise the standards of practice in obstetrics and gynecology. They are the creator of staging criteria to describe the extent and spread of gynecologic malignancies.

label.value: Tumor Suppressor Gene Inactivation Process

value.value: Any DNA sequence alteration process occurring in a tumor suppressor gene, resulting in loss of function of the gene product, and predisposing the cell to neoplastic transformation. Tumor suppressor genes are ordinarily involved in repressing cell cycle or promoting apoptosis. Inactivation of such genes permits growth inappropriately, and is an important step in the process of cellular transformation.

label.value: Milk of Calcium

value.value: Densely calcified fluid, most often found radiographically in association with an obstruction.

label.value: Territory

value.value: A geographical area under the jurisdiction of a sovereign state and marked off for administrative or other purposes.

label.value: British Columbia

value.value: The westernmost Canadian province. Its capital is Victoria.

label.value: Prince Edward Island

value.value: A maritime province of eastern Canada consisting of the island of Prince Edward Island and other nearby islands. Its capital is Charlottetown.

label.value: New Brunswick

value.value: A maritime province of eastern Canada. Its capital is Fredericton.

label.value: Colon Carcinoma Metastatic in the Lung

value.value: A carcinoma that originates from the colonic wall and has spread to the lungs.

label.value: Northwest Territories

value.value: A province in northwest Canada bordering Yukon to the west and Nunavut to the east. Its capital is Yellowknife.

label.value: Nova Scotia

value.value: A Canadian province located on Canada's southeastern coast. Its capital is Halifax.

label.value: Yukon

value.value: A territory in northwest Canada bordering Alaska to the west and the Northwest Territories to the east. Its capital is Whitehorse.

label.value: Alberta

value.value: A province located in western Canada, bounded by British Columbia to the west, Saskatchewan to the east, and the Northwest Territories to the north. Its capital is Edmonton.

label.value: BK Virus

value.value: A double stranded DNA virus in the polyomavirus family. It is widespread but usually causes an asymptomatic infection, except in immunocompromised individuals.

label.value: Transurethral Needle Ablation of the Prostate

value.value: A procedure for treatment of benign prostatic hypertrophy that uses low energy radio frequency energy delivered through the urethra to destroy prostate tissue.

label.value: Gastric Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of gastric cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Tumors arising at the esophagogastric junction, or arising in the stomach in a distance equal or less than 5 cm from the esophagogastric junction and crossing the esophagogastric junction are staged using the TNM system for esophageal adenocarcinoma.  Lymphomas, sarcomas, and carcinoid tumors (low-grade neuroendocrine tumors) are not included in this classification. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Transurethral Microwave Thermotherapy of the Prostate

value.value: A procedure for treatment of benign prostatic hypertrophy that uses microwave energy delivered through the urethra to destroy prostate tissue.

label.value: Osmolality

value.value: The concentration of osmoles of solute per kilogram of solvent present in a sample.

label.value: Trichomonas

value.value: A genus of flagellate protozoa parasitic in birds and mammals, distinguished by the presence of four anterior flagella, an undulating membrane, and a trailing flagellum.

label.value: Iron Polysaccharide

value.value: A delayed-release formulation of iron supplement consisting of an iron atom bound by a polysaccharide molecule. Upon oral administration, there is delayed-release of iron and iron absorption in the stomach and small intestine. The absorbed iron combines with apoferritin to form ferritin, which is stored in the liver, spleen, red bone marrow, and intestinal mucosa. Important in transport of oxygen by hemoglobin to the tissues, iron is also found in myoglobin and transferrin, and is a component of many enzymes such as catalase, peroxidase, and cytochromes. The delayed-release of iron may minimize the gastrointestinal upset caused by iron supplements.

label.value: Gastric Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of gastric cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The pathologic staging depends on data acquired clinically, together with findings on subsequent surgical exploration and examination of the pathologic specimen if resection is accomplished.  Pathologic assessment of the regional lymph nodes entails their removal and histologic examination to evaluate the total number, as well as the number that contain metastatic tumor.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of gastric cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Gram per Week

value.value: A dose administration rate unit equal to the rate at which a gram of a product is delivered or administered over the time period of one week. This is also a unit of mass flow rate equivalent to the rate at which a gram of matter crosses a given surface or is delivered to a given object or space over a period of time equal to one week.

label.value: Microgram per Kilogram per Week

value.value: A dose administration rate unit where the amount of product to be delivered or administered is calculated in micrograms as a function of the subject's weight in kilograms and is delivered or administered over the time period of one week.

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer invading lamina propria, muscularis mucosae, or submucosa. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading lamina propria or muscularis mucosae.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer invading the submucosa. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading the muscularis propria.  A tumor may penetrate the muscularis propria with extension into the gastrocolic or gastrohepatic ligaments, or into the greater or lesser omentum, without perforation of the visceral peritoneum covering these structures. In this case, the tumor is classified T3. If there is perforation of the visceral peritoneum covering the gastric ligaments or the omentum, the tumor should be classified T4. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Postgraduate

value.value: Of, relating to, happening, or engaged in studies beyond a bachelor's degree.

label.value: Residual Volume

value.value: The volume of air remaining in the lungs after a maximal exhalation.

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor penetrating subserosal connective tissue without invasion of visceral peritoneum or adjacent structures.  The adjacent structures of the stomach include the spleen, transverse colon, liver, diaphragm, pancreas, abdominal wall, adrenal gland, kidney, small intestine, and retroperitoneum.  Intramural extension to the duodenum or esophagus is classified by the depth of the greatest invasion in any of these sites, including the stomach. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading serosa (visceral peritoneum) or adjacent structures.  The adjacent structures of the stomach include the spleen, transverse colon, liver, diaphragm, pancreas, abdominal wall, adrenal gland, kidney, small intestine, and retroperitoneum.  Intramural extension to the duodenum or esophagus is classified by the depth of the greatest invasion in any of these sites, including the stomach. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Female Reproductive System Adenofibroma

value.value: A benign or borderline neoplasm characterized by the presence of connective tissue stroma and epithelial structures. It occurs in the ovary, fallopian tube, uterine corpus, and cervix.

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading serosa (visceral peritoneum). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with tumor invading adjacent structures. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Airway

value.value: The part of the respiratory system between the nose or mouth and the lungs.

label.value: Gastric Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of gastric cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer without regional lymph node metastasis.  Note: A designation of pN0 should be used if all examined lymph nodes are negative, regardless of the total number removed and examined. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in 1-2 regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in 3-6 regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in seven or more regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN3a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in 7-15 regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer pN3b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with metastasis in sixteen or more regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Cystadenofibroma

value.value: A benign or borderline neoplasm that arises from the ovaries and the fallopian tubes. It is characterized by the presence of cystic glandular structures and fibrous tissue.

label.value: Gastric Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of gastric cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for gastric cancer. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of gastric cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The clinical staging is based on evidence of extent of disease acquired before definitive treatment is instituted.  It includes physical examination, radiologic imaging, endoscopy, biopsy, and laboratory findings.  All cancers should be confirmed histologically. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of gastric cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Gastric Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Gastric Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Gastric cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
